Since the second derivative $f''(x) = \frac{-2x^{-5/3}}{9}$ is negative
on $(0,\infty)$, the function $f(x)$ is concave down there. Thus, the
tangent line is an over estimate of the function and the true value must
lie in the interval

\begin{align*}
\displaystyle {\color{blue} \left[\frac{23}{12} - \frac{7^{-5/3}}{9},\frac{23}{12}\right]}
\end{align*}
